learner experience across programs and challenges.\n\nWhat we are looking for:\n\nExperience teaching, tutoring, mentoring, or assessing at undergraduate and/or master’s level, or strong professional experience with coaching/feedback in relevant domains.\nDemonstrated ability to provide specific, actionable written feedback against a rubric.\nComfortable supporting students in a fully remote, international environment.\nStrong command of English (written and spoken). Additional languages are a plus.\nConfident using digital tools (e.g., Slack, LMS, Google Workspace, Notion, Zoom) and learning new systems.\nReliable time management; able to work to grading SLAs and fixed weekly hours.\nFamiliarity with AI-assisted workflows for drafting feedback or analyzing rubric alignment (with human oversight).\nExperience with challenge-based learning, competency-based assessment, or portfolio evaluation.\nPrior involvement in curriculum or assessment design.\nBackground or interest in Tomorrow University focus areas (e.g., sustainability, entrepreneurship, tech & innovation, leadership).\n\nWhat Matters to Us\n\nWe’re looking for people who thrive in a dynamic, mission-driven environment. These traits are especially important to us:\n\nOwnership & Independence – You take initiative and get things done\nCollaborative Mindset – You enjoy working across teams and disciplines\nClear & Thoughtful Communication – You know how to adapt your message to different audiences\nIntegrity, Curiosity & Growth – You’re honest, open-minded, and always looking to learn\nProactivity & Drive – You bring energy and momentum to your work\nCommitment to Execution – You don’t just dream big—you make things happen\nPassion for Sustainability, Entrepreneurship & Technology – You care deeply about building a better future\n\nPerks & Benefits\n\nWork from anywhere, anytime\n\nOur flexible work culture gives you the freedom to design your day. Need a change of scenery? We offer a co-working budget so you c