loss financial data.Provides detailed scope and outcome analysis for each opportunity back into the Colt internal business for analysis and learnings.Attends customer meetings in person and remotely. Prepares highly complex service/technical proposals and presentations for Colt products range, leading with our network and security capability.Oversees and participates in regional training and awareness to ensure over time the capability of the region increases, driving yield at a sales team level. To be a thought leader in the market and promote Colt and raise awareness by speaking at trade shows, analyst briefings, etc when requested.Develops, owns and positions the technical sales strategy in written, visual and verbal formats both internally and externally. Identifies and drives strategic opportunities which lead to the penetration of new and low market share accounts, to increase and grow existing revenue and yield. Reviews business plans, sales strategies, develops and executes the technical sales strategy, account planning and development for multi-product opportunities to make sure objectives, goals, win strategies, schedules, and action assignments are clearly defined and aligned to Colts service capabilities.Provides an interface in to the product organisation, to help drive strategy and product improvement. To take customer and market requirements and align to the in region and global product road maps to support.Oversees the creation of an executive summary and customized value proposition designed to penetrate key opportunities, projects and RFPs. Identifies vertical grouping and best practices to train and share across the sales and technical sales communities. Stays abreast of industry trends and assesses market and fosters teamwork and collaboration.Bachelor's degree or equivalent combination of applicable education and experience required; MBA or related graduate degree preferred.Demonstrated technical sales experience (at least 8 years) in telecommun